  <article>
    <h1>My Approach to FHD Retraining</h1>
    <p>My method focuses on retraining the brain's sensory-motor map. Dystonia is viewed not as a muscular defect, but as a "smudging" of the neural representation of the fingers in the motor cortex. By separating movement cues and introducing temporary physical guides (such as splints), we break the old dystonic patterns.</p>
    
    <p>We work on slow, conscious, and pain-free movements. The retraining is highly customized, adapting to each musician's specific instrument, hand anatomy, and symptom presentation, combining kinesiology, ergonomics, and behavioral reinforcement.</p>

    <blockquote>
      "Successful retraining relies on absolute consistency, sensory distinction, and never reinforcing the involuntary clenching during practice."
    </blockquote>
    
    <div style="margin-top: 2rem;">
